'''Marvin Senaya''' (born 28 January 2001) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[right-back]] for {{French football updater|Auxerre}} club [[AJ Auxerre|Auxerre]]. Born in France, he plays for the [[Ghana national football team|Ghana national team]].

==Club career==
Senaya began his senior career with the reserves of [[RC Strasbourg Alsace|Strasbourg]] in 2019, and signed a professional contract with the senior team on 7 May 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sosports.tg/2021/05/07/rc-strasbourg-marvin-senaya-passe-pro/|title=RC Strasbourg : Marvin Senaya passe Pro|date=May 7, 2021|access-date=20 September 2021|archive-date=20 September 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210920212736/https://www.sosports.tg/2021/05/07/rc-strasbourg-marvin-senaya-passe-pro/|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 31 August 2021, Senaya signed on loan with [[FC Sochaux-Montbéliard|Sochaux]] for the 2020–21 season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://fr.news.yahoo.com/foot-transferts-strasbourg-lat%C3%A9ral-marvin-105300941.html|title=Foot - Transferts - Le latéral Marvin Senaya (Strasbourg) a été prêté à Sochaux (Ligue 2)|website=fr.news.yahoo.com}}</ref> He made his professional debut with Sochaux in a 2–0 [[Ligue 2]] win over [[Paris FC]] on 18 September 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2021/09/18/france/ligue-2/fc-sochaux-montbeliard/paris-football-club-98/3525289/|title=Sochaux vs. Paris FC - 18 September 2021|website=Soccerway}}</ref>

Senaya made his [[Ligue 1]] debut for [[RC Strasbourg Alsace|Strasbourg]] on 14 August 2022 against [[OGC Nice|Nice]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Soccerway|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2022/08/14/france/ligue-1/olympique-gymnaste-club-de-nice-cote-dazur/racing-club-de-strasbourg/3802155/|title=Nice v Strasbourg game report|date=14 August 2022|access-date=24 August 2022}}</ref>

On 17 August 2022, Senaya joined [[Rodez AF|Rodez]] on loan.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Rodez|url=https://rodezaveyronfootball.com/ligue-2-bkt-marvin-senaya-neuvieme-recrue-de-la-saison-22-23/|title=MARVIN SENAYA, NEUVIEME RECRUE DE LA SAISON 22/23|date=17 August 2022|access-date=24 August 2022|language=fr}}</ref>

On 6 February 2025, Senaya moved on loan to [[FC Lausanne-Sport|Lausanne-Sport]] in Switzerland.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=FC Lausanne-Sport|url=https://www.lausanne-sport.ch/marvin-senaya-rejoint-le-ls-en-pret-du-rc-strasbourg/|title=Marvin Senaya rejoint le LS en prêt du RC Strasbourg|trans-title=Marvin Senaya joins LS on loan from RC Strasbourg|date=6 February 2025|access-date=6 February 2025|language=fr}}</ref>

On 1 July 2025, Senaya signed a four-year contract with Ligue 1 club [[AJ Auxerre|Auxerre]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-07-01 |title=Official {{!}} Marvin Senaya completes move from Strasbourg to Auxerre - Get French Football News |url=https://www.getfootballnewsfrance.com/2025/official-marvin-senaya-completes-move-from-strasbourg-to-auxerre/ |access-date=2025-07-02 |language=en-US}}</ref>

==International career==
Born in France, Senaya is of Ghanaian and Togolese descent. He was simultaneously called up to the [[Ghana national football team|Ghana national team]] and [[Togo national football team|Togo]] in March 2026, opting to play for Ghana internationally.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://africanfootball.com/news/837336/Senaya-chooses-Ghana-GFA-says|title=Senaya chooses Ghana, GFA says - 2026 FIFA World Cup|website=African Football}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Senaya is the son of the retired Togolese footballer [[Yao Mawuko Sènaya]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sportculture.tg/?p=9208|title=Marvin Senaya : le Franco-togolais passe pro avec Strasbourg - SportCulture|date=June 2, 2021|access-date=20 September 2021|archive-date=20 September 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210920212142/https://sportculture.tg/?p=9208|url-status=dead}}</ref>

